Congratulations go out to our Tom Bean Powerlifting Team!

Sophia Langford placed 4th at the State meet last Saturday and placed 2nd at the Regional meet 2 weeks ago.

Alec Narro who competed in the Regional meet last week, finished 1st in a 3-way tie. Alec will be competing at the State Boys meet this coming Saturday. Alec was also chosen for the THSPA 2nd Team Academic All-State Team.

Abby Farrer was chosen for the THSWPA Elite Team Academic All-State Team.

post_text: Please help us in the fight against cancer this week as we Pink Out Tom Bean. In conjunction with the Tom Bean Booster Club, we will be selling pink balloons for $1 on which we will write a name of a cancer survivor, fighter, or victim. They will be released from the run through tunnel at the football game Friday. You can also invite a Cancer fighter or survivor to walk Fighters Tunnel Walk during halftime of the game when we will release the balloons. All proceeds will go to the Susan G. Komen Foundation. Help support the fight, wear pink and we will see you Friday. Balloons may be purchased at the game.

It's Red Ribbon Week at TBE
Monday: Elect to be drug free. Wear red white and blue. Tuesday: We won't let drugs sneak up on us Wear Camo. Wednesday:Follow your dreams and be drug free. Wear pajamas. post_text: Mrs. Hamilton's 4th grade reading classes have been connecting ficton selection to non fiction selections. Each student read a fiction and nonfiction book and made a connection between them. The blue links are non fiction books and the yellow links are fiction books The white links are the common facts connecting the two books. They then connected them to make a paper chain that ran from the fourth grade rooms all the way to Mrs. Willis 3rd grade room.#TBEPRIDE!

post_text: Nurse Tiffany Yale was recently the featured nurse on our telehealth program. She was able to share with other nurses in the DFW area the benefit of having a doctor available to our students during school hours at no cost to the family. The telehealth program is a doctor visit via the computer with a doctor at Children's Hospital and is available to all of our students. If you would like more information on how to sign your students up for this amazing program, contact Nurse Tiffany at the elementary school. #TBEPRIDE!

post_text: We are excited to share that we are creating a Makerspace in the TBE Library. A makerspace is a place for students to create, invent,tinker, explore and discover using a variety of tools and materials. It is an informal atmosphere that allows learning to unfold. Makerspace will provide students with hands on, creative ways to design, experiment and build as they engage in science, technology and tinkering. If you would like to help, here is a list of items that you can donate. pipe cleaners, googly eyes, clothes pins, beads, paper plates, plastic cups, scrapbooking paper, rubber bands, play dough, legos, water color paints, paint brushes, pom poms , craft sticks, foam shapes, papers sacks, coffee filters. If you have items that you think we might could use, please email marla.shaver@tombean-isd.org. Thank you for your help. #TBEPRIDE!

post_text:
A joint candidate forum for the upcoming elections for the Tom Bean City Council and Tom Bean ISD School Board will be on April 4th at 6:30 in the Middle School Cafeteria.

Butch Henderson, Fannin County District Attorney Administrative Assistant, will moderate the event.

The City Council race has two open seats. Jerry Harris, Daniel Harrison (i) and Lonnie Jones (i) are the candidates.

Tom Bean ISD School Board has three seats open. James Hamilton, Mike Upchurch, Chris Curd (i) and Marion Williams are the candidates for two three year seats. Chris Cook and Beth Hale are the candidates for the single two year seat.

Three questions will be asked to each candidate with a time limit for each response.

May 7th is Election Day with polls open 7am to 7pm.

Early voting starts April 25th and continues through the 29th. Polls are open 8am to 5pm. May 2nd and May 3rd, polls will be open from 7am to 7pm.

All polling will occur at the Tom Bean Community Center. Please mark your calendars for this event and become an informed voter!!
